WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.453 --> 00:00:04.564
[Squawks] <i>♪♪ [Stereo:
Woman Singing Ballad]</i>

2
00:00:04.588 --> 00:00:08.523
<i>♪ The way down
♪ [Clay Gasps] Shit.</i>

3
00:00:08.592 --> 00:00:11.059
<i>♪ To the bottom ♪♪</i>

4
00:00:15.765 --> 00:00:18.366
Ow. Let me.

5
00:00:18.435 --> 00:00:21.987
Come on. Let me do it.

6
00:00:22.056 --> 00:00:23.989
[Sighs]

7
00:00:26.260 --> 00:00:28.227
[Grunts]

8
00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:31.913
Cortisone helping?

9
00:00:31.982 --> 00:00:34.048
I'm fine without it.

10
00:00:35.085 --> 00:00:37.035
I know.

11
00:00:38.405 --> 00:00:39.988
[Gasps]

12
00:00:41.308 --> 00:00:44.526
[Grunts] [Sighs] Good.

13
00:00:46.413 --> 00:00:49.647
When you back? Tomorrow.

14
00:00:54.371 --> 00:00:56.304
Be safe.

15
00:00:57.307 --> 00:00:59.407
Thanks.

16
00:01:00.477 --> 00:01:03.512
<i>♪♪ [Continues. Indistinct]</i>

17
00:01:03.581 --> 00:01:07.032
Maybe some time
away will help you. huh?

18
00:01:07.101 --> 00:01:11.119
<i>Get past whatever this is.</i>

19
00:01:14.792 --> 00:01:16.758
Maybe.

20
00:01:27.604 --> 00:01:30.539
What's the run? Blood drive...

21
00:01:30.607 --> 00:01:33.041
Children's Hospital in Eureka.

22
00:01:34.128 --> 00:01:36.328
Sam Crow. community servants.

23
00:01:36.397 --> 00:01:38.357
That's what we're
all about. baby.

24
00:01:38.382 --> 00:01:40.549
Yeah.

25
00:01:51.795 --> 00:01:55.413
<i>[Abel Crying]</i>

26
00:01:55.482 --> 00:01:57.916
Aw.

27
00:01:57.985 --> 00:02:01.186
My boy. The master of timing.

28
00:02:07.912 --> 00:02:09.944
I love you.

29
00:02:11.765 --> 00:02:14.265
I love you too.

30
00:02:16.636 --> 00:02:18.603
I got him.

31
00:02:24.111 --> 00:02:26.111
[Sighs]

32
00:02:28.015 --> 00:02:29.981
<i>[Crying Stops]</i>

33
00:02:38.575 --> 00:02:40.542
<i>[Footsteps Approaching]</i>

34
00:02:40.610 --> 00:02:42.677
<i>[Jax] Here we go.</i>

35
00:02:42.746 --> 00:02:44.679
[Cooing] Here we go.

36
00:02:52.623 --> 00:02:55.023
What?

37
00:02:56.426 --> 00:02:59.461
I'm your old lady.

38
00:02:59.530 --> 00:03:01.530
[Laughs]

39
00:03:03.267 --> 00:03:06.368
<i>Come on. Let's get you
some breakfast. huh?</i>

40
00:03:06.436 --> 00:03:08.570
<i>Get you big and strong.</i>

41
00:03:12.375 --> 00:03:16.511
<i>♪♪ [Man Singing
Rock. Indistinct]</i>

42
00:03:16.580 --> 00:03:18.513
<i>[Man] Have you got it all?</i>

43
00:03:18.582 --> 00:03:21.583
<i>[Man #2] Yeah. we got everything
we're gonna need... beer. food.</i>

44
00:03:21.652 --> 00:03:25.404
Hey. Didn't know
you were ridin'.

45
00:03:25.472 --> 00:03:28.540
Clay wants me on the relay.

46
00:03:28.609 --> 00:03:32.059
- Mary with the kids?
- The kids are fine. Jax.

47
00:03:32.128 --> 00:03:34.596
- <i>[Motorcycle Revving.</i>
<i>Backfiring]</i>
- Right.

48
00:03:35.682 --> 00:03:37.565
<i>[Chibs]</i> Chitty Chitty Bang Bang.

49
00:03:37.634 --> 00:03:40.836
<i>[Half-Sack] Hey.
all right. [Whistles]</i>

50
00:03:40.904 --> 00:03:43.355
Hey. it's an old fat
boy on an old fat boy.

51
00:03:43.423 --> 00:03:46.858
- <i>Sorry.</i>
- I thought you put
that beast to sleep.

52
00:03:46.927 --> 00:03:49.377
This fat boy ain't even
reached his prime.

53
00:03:49.446 --> 00:03:52.826
- Barely looks like it can
reach the end of the lot.
- Best bike for a long ride.

54
00:03:52.850 --> 00:03:56.051
And I'd put it up against
any of your pretty Dynas.

55
00:03:56.119 --> 00:03:58.536
You hittin' the gay
rodeo on the way?

56
00:03:58.605 --> 00:04:01.055
<i>[Half-Sack] Yee-haw!
[Opie] It's Captain Chaps.</i>

57
00:04:01.124 --> 00:04:03.542
- <i>[Laughter]</i>
- Cowhide can take the man-hide.

58
00:04:03.610 --> 00:04:06.078
<i>[Tig] Get in line. Brokeback.</i>

59
00:04:07.814 --> 00:04:10.699
<i>[Half-Sack] Oh.
man. really? [Jax] Shit!</i>

60
00:04:10.767 --> 00:04:14.686
Aw. goddamn. man. Come
on. I gotta ride behind that thing?

61
00:04:14.755 --> 00:04:18.590
Shut up. You should be used to
getting sprayed in the face. Prospect.

62
00:04:18.658 --> 00:04:21.108
<i>[Jax] Usually by
Bobby.</i> Eat me. Chibs.

63
00:04:21.177 --> 00:04:24.279
The thing is. I like a full scrote
when I snack on someone.

64
00:04:24.347 --> 00:04:26.715
- <i>Tasty.</i>
- Oh. is that right? Yeah.

65
00:04:26.783 --> 00:04:29.901
Okay. well. pretty
soon you can have that.

66
00:04:29.970 --> 00:04:32.970
- Are you gonna spontaneously
sprout a nut?
- <i>[Jax] Boing.</i>

67
00:04:33.039 --> 00:04:36.091
No. <i>[Jax] What.
what. what. what?</i>

68
00:04:37.144 --> 00:04:39.061
- Gettin' a neuticle.
- Gettin' a what?

69
00:04:39.129 --> 00:04:41.657
<i>[Bobby] You're gettin'
a musical? Musical?</i>

70
00:04:41.681 --> 00:04:43.649
A fake ball. A
neuticle. It's an implant.

71
00:04:43.717 --> 00:04:46.018
Give me a sense of
symmetry. Balance.

72
00:04:46.086 --> 00:04:48.170
<i>- [Laughter]
- Are you for real?</i>

73
00:04:48.238 --> 00:04:51.172
Oh. yeah. I'm just waitin' for
the V.A. insurance to clear.

74
00:04:51.241 --> 00:04:53.386
You're getting a
glass ball? <i>No. no.</i>

75
00:04:53.410 --> 00:04:55.688
It's not glass. It's
like a... What is it?

76
00:04:55.712 --> 00:04:59.347
It feels real. Like. uh.
soft. you know? Squishy.

77
00:04:59.416 --> 00:05:01.244
Like. it's not...
Like a real ball.

78
00:05:01.268 --> 00:05:03.785
[Mooing]

79
00:05:03.854 --> 00:05:06.365
I don't even know... Come on. I
don't even know what that means.

80
00:05:06.389 --> 00:05:09.023
<i>[Indistinct] It's
modern technology.</i>

81
00:05:09.092 --> 00:05:11.026
<i>[Chattering]</i>

82
00:05:11.095 --> 00:05:13.656
Try to be open here.
okay? I'll be gentle.

83
00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:15.613
Okay. real mature. guys.

84
00:05:16.516 --> 00:05:18.684
Yeah. you're a class act. Chibs.

85
00:05:19.770 --> 00:05:22.137
- What?
- You don't wanna know.

86
00:05:22.205 --> 00:05:24.139
Really.

87
00:05:24.207 --> 00:05:26.491
- Hey. Bobby.
- Yeah?

88
00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:29.160
<i>Shoulder gonna hold up?</i>
Yeah. the shoulder's good.

89
00:05:33.233 --> 00:05:35.967
<i>Hey. uh. appreciate you takin'
care of the garage while I'm gone.</i>

90
00:05:36.036 --> 00:05:39.015
- No problem.
- Tell the boys
they can log some O.T.

91
00:05:39.039 --> 00:05:42.524
- I don't wanna get buried.
- <i>I'll keep an eye on her.</i>

92
00:05:42.593 --> 00:05:45.476
I. uh... I know she's
been... She's fine.

93
00:05:47.081 --> 00:05:49.381
You just worry about the cars.

94
00:05:50.434 --> 00:05:52.366
They got my full attention.

95
00:06:00.544 --> 00:06:03.478
What do you say. Prez?
Let's go save the children.

96
00:06:06.232 --> 00:06:08.817
- [Cheering]
- Come on. boys!

97
00:06:08.885 --> 00:06:11.385
<i>♪♪ [Rock Beat]</i>

98
00:06:11.455 --> 00:06:14.172
<i>[Shouting. Cheering]</i>

99
00:06:20.681 --> 00:06:23.198
<i>[Man] ♪ We're going riding ♪</i>

100
00:06:24.501 --> 00:06:27.018
<i>♪ In the neighborhood ♪</i>

101
00:06:27.086 --> 00:06:29.971
[Car Alarm Beeping] <i> ♪
We're gonna be free. yeah ♪♪</i>

102
00:06:31.141 --> 00:06:33.691
<i>♪♪ [Continues. Indistinct]</i>

103
00:06:48.175 --> 00:06:50.291
<i>[Man] ♪ Riding
through this world ♪</i>

104
00:06:51.745 --> 00:06:53.978
<i>♪ All alone ♪</i>

105
00:06:54.047 --> 00:06:56.248
<i>♪ God takes your soul ♪</i>

106
00:06:57.301 --> 00:06:59.383
<i>♪ You're on your own ♪</i>

107
00:07:00.603 --> 00:07:03.638
<i>♪ The crow flies straight ♪</i>

108
00:07:03.707 --> 00:07:06.157
<i>♪ A perfect line ♪</i>

109
00:07:06.225 --> 00:07:09.043
<i>♪ On the devil's bed ♪</i>

110
00:07:09.112 --> 00:07:11.630
<i>♪ Until you die ♪</i>

111
00:07:13.400 --> 00:07:15.684
<i>♪ Gotta look this life ♪</i>

112
00:07:17.070 --> 00:07:19.287
<i>♪ In the eye ♪♪</i>

113
00:07:26.546 --> 00:07:28.863
<i>♪♪ [Rock Beat]</i>

114
00:07:28.932 --> 00:07:31.365
<i>[Man] ♪ Mmm. yeah ♪</i>

115
00:07:39.409 --> 00:07:42.076
<i>♪♪ [Man Singing. Indistinct]</i>

116
00:08:15.411 --> 00:08:18.479
<i>♪♪ [Fades. Ends]</i>

117
00:08:18.548 --> 00:08:21.449
Military surplus as cover...
Wish we thought of that.

118
00:08:21.518 --> 00:08:24.469
- It's Edmond. Boy's a genius.
- <i>[Chibs] Oh. yeah?</i>

119
00:08:24.537 --> 00:08:26.520
Must take after his mother.

120
00:08:26.589 --> 00:08:29.240
Obviously.

121
00:08:29.309 --> 00:08:31.859
- <i>[Clay] How do we carry?</i>
- Ten guns in each.

122
00:08:31.929 --> 00:08:34.296
Roll it up. Strap it on.

123
00:08:34.364 --> 00:08:36.375
Just a biker with a bedroll.

124
00:08:36.399 --> 00:08:39.918
Six riders. five dozen.
That's a good haul.

125
00:08:39.987 --> 00:08:43.170
<i>Runs are set up for the next
three months. One every two weeks.</i>

126
00:08:43.239 --> 00:08:45.935
<i>We try to cover as many runs
as we can with charity rides.</i>

127
00:08:45.959 --> 00:08:49.477
<i>Cops never mess with us
when we're... serving humanity.</i>

128
00:08:49.546 --> 00:08:52.408
<i>Rest of the time. travel in
twos. stay off the main roads...</i>

129
00:08:52.432 --> 00:08:54.366
Should be no problem.

130
00:08:54.434 --> 00:08:58.169
The 32... Real pleased the way
this worked out with Sam Crow.

131
00:08:58.238 --> 00:09:00.771
Well. you tell the
scabby fence boys...

132
00:09:00.840 --> 00:09:02.757
I'm all about the cause.

133
00:09:02.826 --> 00:09:05.994
You can tell 'em yourself.
<i>[Cameron] Edmond.</i>

134
00:09:10.383 --> 00:09:12.984
Jimmy O. some of
the Falcarragh crew...

135
00:09:13.053 --> 00:09:15.553
might be comin'
stateside. time allows.

136
00:09:20.977 --> 00:09:23.979
[Speaking Irish Dialect]

137
00:09:25.315 --> 00:09:27.849
Their day will come.

138
00:09:31.304 --> 00:09:33.254
<i>[Telephone Ringing]</i>

139
00:09:34.991 --> 00:09:36.924
Oh. shit.

140
00:09:38.661 --> 00:09:41.262
Yeah? Hold on.

141
00:09:41.331 --> 00:09:45.150
- Mail.
- Just drop it there.

142
00:09:45.218 --> 00:09:48.069
Anything I can do?

143
00:09:48.137 --> 00:09:50.450
Hunt down the keys to the
gold Sebring. <i>Sure. darlin'.</i>

144
00:09:50.474 --> 00:09:52.424
Right this way. sweet cheeks.

145
00:09:52.492 --> 00:09:54.942
Thanks. Hmm.

146
00:09:55.011 --> 00:09:57.412
<i>♪♪ [Radio: Man
Singing Rock. Faint]</i>

147
00:10:18.251 --> 00:10:20.801
<i>[Indistinct Conversations]</i>

148
00:10:45.945 --> 00:10:47.862
Good morning.

149
00:10:47.931 --> 00:10:50.532
You looking for Sherman's?

150
00:10:50.600 --> 00:10:52.717
They closed last month.

151
00:10:52.786 --> 00:10:55.303
Hope it wasn't a return.

152
00:11:12.238 --> 00:11:14.172
Sorry. ma'am.

153
00:11:19.428 --> 00:11:21.763
[No Audible Dialogue]

154
00:11:31.424 --> 00:11:34.091
<i>[Horn Honks]</i>

155
00:11:36.746 --> 00:11:39.496
<i>[Woman] 'Scuse
me. Are you leaving?</i>

156
00:11:41.467 --> 00:11:43.735
<i>[Horn Honks]</i>

157
00:11:45.772 --> 00:11:48.506
<i>- [Brakes Screech]
- [Horn Honks]</i>

158
00:11:48.575 --> 00:11:50.452
Are you leaving. or what?

159
00:11:50.476 --> 00:11:52.726
<i>[Horn Honks]</i>

160
00:11:54.264 --> 00:11:57.548
- [Hammer Clicks]
- Oh. shit!

161
00:12:05.741 --> 00:12:08.676
<i>♪♪ [Mid-tempo Heavy Metal Beat]</i>

162
00:12:34.404 --> 00:12:36.437
<i>[Man] ♪ Now ♪</i>

163
00:12:41.944 --> 00:12:45.329
[Engine Backfiring]

164
00:12:48.701 --> 00:12:50.461
- [Tires Squealing]
- [Yells]

165
00:12:51.187 --> 00:12:52.770
- Come on!
- [Backfires]

166
00:12:53.673 --> 00:12:56.457
[Groans]

167
00:12:56.526 --> 00:12:59.293
- <i>[Tires Squealing]</i>
- Oh. shit!

168
00:12:59.362 --> 00:13:01.161
[Clay] Hey! Who's down?

169
00:13:02.465 --> 00:13:04.415
[Half-Sack] Tig! Tig!

170
00:13:12.325 --> 00:13:15.026
Tig. you all right?
Shit. Tig. Tig!

171
00:13:17.413 --> 00:13:19.346
<i>[Car Door Opens]</i>

172
00:13:32.779 --> 00:13:34.946
I got a disturbing
call from a woman.

173
00:13:35.014 --> 00:13:38.077
Says you pulled a
gun on her. [Laughs]

174
00:13:38.101 --> 00:13:40.652
Yeah.

175
00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:43.670
That's it? Just... yeah?

176
00:13:43.739 --> 00:13:46.641
I didn't shoot her.

177
00:13:48.295 --> 00:13:50.662
Wh-What the hell am I
supposed to do with that?

178
00:13:56.452 --> 00:13:58.786
You gonna hit a
bank or something?

179
00:14:01.107 --> 00:14:04.392
It's what they were
wearing. Who?

180
00:14:05.995 --> 00:14:07.978
Oh. Jesus.

181
00:14:08.047 --> 00:14:10.781
Yeah. someone dropped
it in our mailbox today...

182
00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:12.850
In the Sherman's bag.

183
00:14:13.953 --> 00:14:16.820
They're just
trying to rattle you.

184
00:14:17.891 --> 00:14:21.409
Sherman's. Holy shit. Zobelle.

185
00:14:21.478 --> 00:14:24.011
Look. I'm sorry about the gun.

186
00:14:25.398 --> 00:14:27.798
Come on. Lemme...
Lemme take you home.

187
00:14:32.772 --> 00:14:34.706
There's somethin' I
gotta do. <i>[Engine Starts]</i>

188
00:14:34.774 --> 00:14:37.654
I'll be okay. Whoa. whoa.
whoa. Wanna give me the gun?

189
00:14:39.128 --> 00:14:42.846
Sure. I'll return it later.

190
00:14:54.327 --> 00:14:56.711
He's stable. Get
him to Admitting.

191
00:14:56.780 --> 00:14:59.112
- Sorry. man.
- You just get patched up.

192
00:14:59.181 --> 00:15:01.160
<i>We'll come by after the drop.</i>

193
00:15:01.184 --> 00:15:03.117
I'm gonna shove that
bike so far up your ass...

194
00:15:04.187 --> 00:15:07.922
Gonna be just... fine.

195
00:15:07.991 --> 00:15:10.975
<i>You tend to his
every beck and call.</i>

196
00:15:11.044 --> 00:15:14.928
Wipe his goddamn ass. if
that's what he wants you to do.

197
00:15:14.997 --> 00:15:18.482
Call Piney. Tell him we got two
bikes down. Gonna need the flatbed.

198
00:15:18.551 --> 00:15:20.735
That's you. Call Piney.

199
00:15:24.090 --> 00:15:25.856
I got it. I can take it.

200
00:15:25.925 --> 00:15:28.225
I said I got it.

201
00:15:32.899 --> 00:15:35.093
What the hell are you talkin'
about. you can't take him?

202
00:15:35.117 --> 00:15:37.095
Mr. Trager has basic coverage.

203
00:15:37.119 --> 00:15:39.632
<i>He can only be admitted
to a hospital in his plan.</i>

204
00:15:39.656 --> 00:15:41.806
He's bleedin' in your hallway.

205
00:15:41.874 --> 00:15:43.669
I'm sorry. We'll have to
transfer him to Red Bluff.

206
00:15:43.693 --> 00:15:46.026
He's stable enough to travel.

207
00:15:46.095 --> 00:15:48.028
How about you give
him some pain meds?

208
00:15:48.097 --> 00:15:50.378
I can give him some Advil.

209
00:15:51.334 --> 00:15:53.767
He's got a gash the size
of your attitude on his leg.

210
00:15:53.836 --> 00:15:56.303
Got enough Advil for that?

211
00:15:57.607 --> 00:16:01.526
<i>How much longer?</i> There's
good news and bad news.

212
00:16:01.594 --> 00:16:03.594
You're stable enough to travel.

213
00:16:03.663 --> 00:16:05.929
What do you mean? Travel where?

214
00:16:05.998 --> 00:16:09.200
Well. that's the bad news. We
gotta move you to another hospital.

215
00:16:09.269 --> 00:16:12.603
- H.M.O. bullshit!
- Christ. Come on.

216
00:16:12.672 --> 00:16:15.539
Stitch me up!

217
00:16:15.608 --> 00:16:17.491
Sons of bitches!

218
00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:20.861
Call Red Bluff. We need this
guy shuttled... Quicker. the better.

219
00:16:20.930 --> 00:16:25.166
Okay. <i>[Man On P.A.]
Orderly to the blood bank.</i>

220
00:16:26.502 --> 00:16:29.787
Hey. it's me. Run this name
through your database?

221
00:16:29.856 --> 00:16:31.989
Alexander Trager.

222
00:16:37.280 --> 00:16:39.781
[Bell Dings]

223
00:16:39.849 --> 00:16:42.533
<i>♪♪ [P.A.: Classical]</i>

224
00:16:42.601 --> 00:16:44.735
Oh. Chief.

225
00:16:46.206 --> 00:16:48.400
We're. uh. not
open for a few days.

226
00:16:48.424 --> 00:16:50.925
but is there something
I can help you with?

227
00:16:52.061 --> 00:16:54.028
Not lookin' for smokes.

228
00:16:56.098 --> 00:16:59.233
I know who you are. What you do.

229
00:16:59.302 --> 00:17:02.536
If you're referring to the League
of American Nationalists...

230
00:17:02.605 --> 00:17:05.645
I'm not talkin' about what
you do with a suit and tie.

231
00:17:07.326 --> 00:17:10.428
I'm talking about what you
do with the rubber masks.

232
00:17:10.496 --> 00:17:13.881
I'm afraid you
have me at a loss.

233
00:17:13.950 --> 00:17:16.651
Things work themselves around.

234
00:17:18.187 --> 00:17:21.672
Your time will come.

235
00:17:21.741 --> 00:17:24.942
That sounds like a threat.

